            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x9EA3CAD7<!--String: "I've got some rabbits and birds helping out with my garden. The rabbits do their business and fertilize the plants, and the birds sing to the little sprouts. Plants are social creatures too, you know!"--></T>
                  <T>0x8F1A4518<!--String: "Why not get the children involved in gardening? Teach them about plants. Let them get their hands dirty. It's good for their minds."--></T>
                  <T>0x96EA1CB2<!--String: "It may go without saying, but if you want to grow an oversized crop, they need room to breathe. You can't just shove them into one of those little planters. Make sure they have their own gardening patch."--></T>
                  <T>0x408C5E6C<!--String: "Where do you get seeds? Well, obviously from the Crumplebottom Garden Stall in Finchwick. I suppose you could shop on the computer or order them through a grocery delivery service, but why buy from anywhere but the best? Perhaps I'm biased."--></T>
                  <T>0x6A2343E7<!--String: "It's all rather simple. Pruning is important. Watering is essential. Fertilizer! Well, there are multiple types of fertilizer. Some make your plants grow quicker or healthier. Others improve quality. Some cause the plant to produce more fruit. It's important to use the right fertilizer to fit your needs. So, not so simple then."--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
        <L n="tests">
          <L>
            <V t="trait">
              <U n="trait">
                <E n="subject">TargetSim</E>
                <L n="whitelist_traits">
                  <T>260169<!--Trait: trait_Hidden_CottageWorld_NPC_AgathaCrumplebottom--></T>
                  <T>259314<!--Trait: trait_Hidden_CottageWorld_NPC_AgnesCrumplebottom--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
          </L>
        </L>
      </U>
