            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x67EBE78E<!--String: "The happier your animals are, the higher quality goods they'll produce. If you want nice eggs, keep happy chickens! Quality milk comes from well-socialized cows. And the fluffiest of wools grows on the cleanest of llamas."--></T>
                  <T>0x40D82007<!--String: "The critters love it when you spend time with them. I speak to them all the time. I tell them about my day. About what I ate. Dates I've gone on... that were awkward... and regretful — uh, where were we? The critters! Right. Yes, very good listeners."--></T>
                  <T>0xAC9CE39D<!--String: "Rabbits, birds, and foxes love to get gifts! Well, don't we all? If you want to get close to one of them, try figuring out what gifts it likes. Before you know it, it might be bringing you gifts from the woods, too."--></T>
                  <T>0x7A600893<!--String: "Those foxes can be quite sly but I once saw a rooster take one on - beak primed, knives out, feathers flying - and give it what for, such that the fox had to admit defeat and slunk off in shame!"--></T>
                  <T>0x59A49FBA<!--String: "No one enjoys being spit on, not really, and that includes foxes! If you've been having some fox troubles, having a llama in the right place to gob that bandit could be just the ticket."--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
