                  <T>0x22B4356D<!--String: "Sims always come to me for life advice. You know what I tell them? Take it slow. Sometimes you try to do life on fast-forward and your needs get out of hand."--></T>
                  <T>0x43DFBC13<!--String: "You know what my Nan used to say? When times were hard, she'd say, 'This too shall pass.' And she was always right. She also said, 'It's a poor mother bird who has a poo in their own nest.' Which is also true, but probably not directly applicable advice right now."--></T>
                  <T>0x51610022<!--String: "If you truly want to live your best life, there's a lot to learn from the creatures. Take the clever foxes we see around here. They're adaptable, perceptive, strategic, persistent — sometimes a touch too much. Be like the fox and you are bound to succeed."--></T>
                  <T>0x7A600893<!--String: "Those foxes can be quite sly but I once saw a rooster take one on - beak primed, knives out, feathers flying - and give it what for, such that the fox had to admit defeat and slunk off in shame!"--></T>
